definitions.definition: A small mechanically produced piece ( chip ) of wood, generally from 0.5 to 10 cm in diameter , used primarily as raw material for pulp , paper and construction boards , as well as fuel and mulch .
A small fibre of wood ; especially such material as used to make ingrain wallpaper , aka woodchip wallpaper .
